abstract: Mr. Bloomberg’s proposal, which would offer a government alternative to private health insurance, is similar to plans from some of his more moderate rivals in the 2020 race.
snippet: Mr. Bloomberg’s proposal, which would offer a government alternative to private health insurance, is similar to plans from some of his more moderate rivals in the 2020 race.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Former Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg of New York unveiled a health policy proposal on Thursday that would create a government-run health insurance plan but not provide universal guaranteed coverage, aligning himself with the more moderate wing of the Democratic Party in the 2020 presidential primary.

abstract: President Vladimir Putin on Thursday rejected allegations of Russian interference in British politics and praised Prime Minister Boris Johnson for better understanding the mood of British society on Brexit than his political rivals.
snippet: President Vladimir Putin on Thursday rejected allegations of Russian interference in British politics and praised Prime Minister Boris Johnson for better understanding the mood of British society on Brexit than his political rivals.
lead_paragraph: MOSCOW — President Vladimir Putin on Thursday rejected allegations of Russian interference in British politics and praised Prime Minister Boris Johnson for better understanding the mood of British society on Brexit than his political rivals.
headline_main: Putin Rejects Charges of Russian Meddling in UK Politics, Praises Johnson
headline_print_headline: Putin Rejects Charges of Russian Meddling in UK Politics, Praises Johnson

abstract: The leader of Catalonia's regional government Quim Torra said on Thursday he would appeal a ruling by the Spanish region's highest court that convicted him of disobedience and banned him from holding public office for 18 months.
snippet: The leader of Catalonia's regional government Quim Torra said on Thursday he would appeal a ruling by the Spanish region's highest court that convicted him of disobedience and banned him from holding public office for 18 months.
lead_paragraph: BARCELONA — The leader of Catalonia's regional government Quim Torra said on Thursday he would appeal a ruling by the Spanish region's highest court that convicted him of disobedience and banned him from holding public office for 18 months.
headline_main: Catalan Leader Torra Says to Appeal Conviction for Disobedience
headline_print_headline: Catalan Leader Torra Says to Appeal Conviction for Disobedience

abstract: The United States has imposed sanctions on two Iranian judges whom it accuses of having punished Iranian citizens and dual nationals for exercising their freedoms of speech and assembly, the U.S. Treasury said on Thursday.
snippet: The United States has imposed sanctions on two Iranian judges whom it accuses of having punished Iranian citizens and dual nationals for exercising their freedoms of speech and assembly, the U.S. Treasury said on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The United States has imposed sanctions on two Iranian judges whom it accuses of having punished Iranian citizens and dual nationals for exercising their freedoms of speech and assembly, the U.S. Treasury said on Thursday.
headline_main: U.S. Imposes Sanctions on Two Iranian Judges for 'Oppression'
headline_print_headline: U.S. Imposes Sanctions on Two Iranian Judges for 'Oppression'

abstract: Ms. Warren will meet with several tribes in the state where she grew up, part of her continuing outreach efforts in the wake of the controversy over her past claims of Native heritage.
snippet: Ms. Warren will meet with several tribes in the state where she grew up, part of her continuing outreach efforts in the wake of the controversy over her past claims of Native heritage.
lead_paragraph: Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts will meet with several Native American tribes in Oklahoma on Sunday morning, continuing her efforts to reach out to tribal communities during her presidential campaign and further quell the controversy she ignited years ago by claiming Native American ancestry, for which she has apologized.

abstract: Iraqi lawmakers said on Thursday that deadlock in parliament was holding up the selection of an interim prime minister, meaning leaders would miss a deadline to name a replacement for Adel Abdul Mahdi and prolong nationwide unrest.
snippet: Iraqi lawmakers said on Thursday that deadlock in parliament was holding up the selection of an interim prime minister, meaning leaders would miss a deadline to name a replacement for Adel Abdul Mahdi and prolong nationwide unrest.
lead_paragraph: BAGHDAD — Iraqi lawmakers said on Thursday that deadlock in parliament was holding up the selection of an interim prime minister, meaning leaders would miss a deadline to name a replacement for Adel Abdul Mahdi and prolong nationwide unrest.
headline_main: Political Deadlock Delays Choice of New PM to Steer Iraq Out of Crisis
headline_print_headline: Political Deadlock Delays Choice of New PM to Steer Iraq Out of Crisis

abstract: British Prime Minister Boris Johnson set out his government's legislative agenda on Thursday, describing it as "the most radical Queen's Speech in a generation".
snippet: British Prime Minister Boris Johnson set out his government's legislative agenda on Thursday, describing it as "the most radical Queen's Speech in a generation".
lead_paragraph: LONDON — British Prime Minister Boris Johnson set out his government's legislative agenda on Thursday, describing it as "the most radical Queen's Speech in a generation".
headline_main: UK PM Johnson Promises 'Most Radical' Agenda in a Generation
headline_print_headline: UK PM Johnson Promises 'Most Radical' Agenda in a Generation

abstract: Canada’s highest court ruled that the son of the Russian spies whose story helped inspire a hit TV series is entitled to citizenship.
snippet: Canada’s highest court ruled that the son of the Russian spies whose story helped inspire a hit TV series is entitled to citizenship.
lead_paragraph: MONTREAL — It has all the makings of a Cold War drama: Russian sleeper spies posing as a suburban family in North America, children who say they were oblivious their parents were Russian agents and an elaborate F.B.I. operation unmasking the shadowy ruse.

abstract: Britain will introduce a new law on espionage to counter the threat from potentially 'hostile' states such as Russia and China after the 2018 chemical attack on a former Russian double agent that London blamed on Russian military intelligence.
snippet: Britain will introduce a new law on espionage to counter the threat from potentially 'hostile' states such as Russia and China after the 2018 chemical attack on a former Russian double agent that London blamed on Russian military intelligence.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Britain will introduce a new law on espionage to counter the threat from potentially 'hostile' states such as Russia and China after the 2018 chemical attack on a former Russian double agent that London blamed on Russian military intelligence.
headline_main: Britain to Bolster Spy Defenses Against Russia and China After 2018 Chemical Attack

abstract: Britain's Queen Elizabeth set out Prime Minister Boris Johnson's legislative agenda on Thursday, outlining Brexit and the National Health Service (NHS) as the government's main priorities.
